@alexander-akait Thanks for the response. Yes 2 and 3 full size is about the same, but I'm confused about 
>Webpack move rxjs inside one chunk because it is better for code splitting

Code in the main chunk needs to be downloaded up front by the browser, which adds latency and hurts parse time. Shouldn't webpack be treeshaking `rxjs` out of the main bundle in the third case, since it is never statically imported?

Earlier I had done something like this
```ts
import webpack, { Configuration } from "webpack";
import { merge } from "webpack-merge";

const isProduction = process.env.NODE_ENV === "production";

module.exports = () => {
  const devOptions: Configuration = {
          static: {
              directory: PATHS.dist
          },
          port: 8888,
