I managed to find a workaround. Thanks so much to @ScriptedAlchemy for the help on this.

Essentially I'm finding chunks that are both entrypoints and runtimes of a group and I mark them as initial.

```
class MarkWorkerAsInitialPlugin {
    constructor() { }
    /**
     * Apply the plugin
     * @param {import('webpack').Compiler} compiler the compiler instance
     * @returns {void}
     */
    apply(compiler) {
        compiler.hooks.compilation.tap('MarkWorkerAsInitialPlugin', (compilation) => {
            compilation.hooks.optimizeChunks.tap('MarkWorkerAsInitialPlugin', (chunks) => {
                for (const chunk of chunks) {
                    for (const chunkGroup of chunk.groupsIterable) {
                        if (chunkGroup._entrypointChunk === chunkGroup._runtimeChunk) {
                            chunkGroup._initial = true;
                        }
                    }
                }
            });
        });
    }
}
```

I'm interested in finding out a way to do this inside webpack's code, so we can mark these entrypoints as initial if we're using module federation (or maybe this is another condition we might have to check when generating the module federation runtime)

