The issue has been finally resolved as follows, instead of using the standard import in the reference.

Original:

```typescript
import puppeteer, {Browser, PaperFormat, PDFOptions, Viewport} from 'puppeteer';
```

Change to:

```typescript
import {Browser, PaperFormat, PDFOptions, Viewport} from 'puppeteer-core/lib/cjs/puppeteer/puppeteer-core.js';
import puppeteer from 'puppeteer/lib/cjs/puppeteer/puppeteer.js';
```

it works for me. @rdsedmundo 

And, finally, use the follows:

```typescript
// all types import, will be removed after compilation
import {Browser, PaperFormat, PDFOptions, Viewport} from 'puppeteer';
// use require, not import
const puppeteer = require('puppeteer');
```

the reason is if use `import`, webpack will use the esm version to compile, which leads the error. here is the `package.json` of puppeteer:

