So the original code

```ts
function num() { return 1 }

function print() {
  let a = num();

  try {
    let b = 2;
    console.warn(b)
  } finally {
    console.warn(a)
  }
}
```

will be built to

```ts

function num() {
  return 1;
}
function print() {
  let n = num();
  try {
    let n = 2;
    console.warn(n);
  } finally {
    console.warn(n);
  }
}

```

terser@5.16.4 will use the same variable `n`

