```diff
+ import "react-datepicker/dist/react-datepicker.css";
- import "react-datepicker/src/stylesheets/datepicker.scss"
```
> As for why it stopped working after migrating to Webpack v5:
react-datepicker only declares *.css files as having side effects in its package.json ŌĆö it does not include *.scss.
So when you import the .scss directly (e.g. import 'react-datepicker/src/stylesheets/datepicker.scss'), Webpack v5 may treat it as a side-effect-free module and tree-shake it, assuming itŌĆÖs safe to remove.

If you still prefer to keep your current import style (e.g. importing SCSS directly), you can adjust your webpack.config.js like this to ensure those styles aren't tree-shaken:
```diff
module.exports = {
  // ... your existing config
  module: {
    rules: [
      {
        test: /\.scss$/,
        use: ['style-loader', 'css-loader', 'sass-loader'],
        // Mark SCSS files as having side effects
+        sideEffects: true
      }
    ]
  }
};

```

