- Using `script` tag
- As you said above `setting optimization.runtimeChunk to true and concatenating every entry with it's runtime would do the trick`
- Setup `publicPath` to any other value different from `"auto"`
- Put `define.js` in the `eglebegle` directory (your example)
- Make own logic for `AutoPublicPathRuntimeModule`) (`__webpack_require__.p`) using `compilation.hooks.runtimeRequirementInTree` hook, you can just inject your own logic and manipulate with `__webpack_require__.p`

