@Timeless0911 Thanks for the feedback. It seems this issue canŌĆÖt be easily solved by webpack alone, because webpack canŌĆÖt determine which identifiers within the same scope should be renamed and which shouldnŌĆÖt. Below is my short summary of the problem.

### Problem
Loaders like `react-refresh-webpack-plugin` inject runtime code that accesses webpack globals (`__webpack_require__`, `__webpack_exports__`). When the source code is a webpack-bundled library from npm containing local declarations with the same names, webpack's `CompatibilityPlugin` renames ALL references in that scope, breaking the loader-injected code.

Example (loader injects code before and after the library code):
```javascript
// Loader: injected BEFORE library code
__webpack_require__.setupRefresh = function() { /* ... */ };

// Library: webpack-bundled code from npm
var __webpack_require__ = {};
__webpack_require__.d = function() { /* ... */ };
__webpack_exports__.MyApp = () => {};

// Loader: injected AFTER library code  
__webpack_require__.cleanupRefresh = function() { /* ... */ };
```

After webpack processing (ŌØī broken):
```javascript
// Both injected references are incorrectly renamed
__nested_webpack_require_106__.setupRefresh = function() { /* ... */ };

var __nested_webpack_require_106__ = {};
__nested_webpack_require_106__.d = function() { /* ... */ };
__nested_webpack_export_106__.MyApp = () => {};

__nested_webpack_require_106__.cleanupRefresh = function() { /* ... */ };
```

**Why?** Webpack processes code AFTER loaders run. Everything is in the same scope, so webpack cannot distinguish loader-injected code from library code.

### Solution
Use `/* webpackNoRename: true */` magic comment:

```javascript
// Ō£ģ Preserved
/* webpackNoRename: true */ __webpack_require__.setupRefresh = function() { /* ... */ };

var __nested_webpack_require_106__ = {};
__nested_webpack_require_106__.d = function() { /* ... */ };
__nested_webpack_export_106__.MyApp = () => {};

// Ō£ģ Preserved
/* webpackNoRename: true */ __webpack_require__.cleanupRefresh = function() { /* ... */ };
```

