in the meantime this is the vibe coded patch they say solves the issue locally (i didn't test this - but perhaps it provides some hint to you)

> ## Root cause
>The Inter .woff2 is referenced from both CSS (fonts/Inter/inter.pcss) and JS
(evo-roulette-new/src/common/assets/const.ts). On the lobby build the asset module is emitted
CSS-only. On the next (game) build, webpack's incremental moduleMemCaches2 decides the asset
module is "unchanged" ŌĆö it only compares outgoing connections ŌĆö so it reuses the cached module
hash, skips NormalModule.updateHash, and never re-runs the _sourceTypes reset from upstream fix
[#20801](https://github.com/webpack/webpack/pull/20801). Result: no JS code factory is generated for
the asset, and __webpack_require__ throws at runtime. AssetGenerator.getTypes() derives its
output from incoming origin types (CSS vs JS) ŌĆö the one input the cache wasn't tracking.
>## Fix
>Patch lib/Compilation.js (.yarn/patches/webpack.patch) so the affected-modules check also tracks
each asset module's incoming origin-type signature. When a CSS-only asset becomes JS-referenced,
its cache entry is invalidated, the hash recomputes, and the upstream _sourceTypes fix fires ŌĆö
producing the JS factory in the new chunk. Asset-gated, so JS/CSS modules pay only one string check.

```diff
