This is due:
```json
      "require": {
        "module": "./modules/index-all.js",
        "browser": {
          "production": "./underscore-umd-min.js",
          "default": "./underscore-umd.js"
        },
        "node": "./underscore-node.cjs",
        "default": "./underscore-umd.js"
      }
```

webpack takes `module`, NodeJS takes `node`, changing it will have a big breaking change, you can do it manually by setup `conditionNames`, note - you can override it only for cjs using `resolve.byDependency.commonjs.conditionNames`, to be honestly this exports is a little bit wrong, it should be:

```json
{
  // ...
  "module": "./modules/index-all.js", 
  "default": "./underscore-umd.js"
}
```

`module` is like a fallback, something like a `default`, specific scenarios must come first, `node` is more specific than `module`

